The paper deals with probability distributions and their applications in computer science. Specifically, it discusses the Poisson Multinomial Distribution (PMD) and its properties, including a Central Limit Theorem (CLT) and its applications in game theory and learning theory. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Game Theory (cs.GT), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
